bsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">The team is your family, and until you graduate, your university&rsquo;s athletic program is your home. It&rsquo;s okay to have a period of &lsquo;displacement&rsquo; as you adjust to your new athletic family. Many players face low-level depression, loneliness, and stress when adjusting to a transfer.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Taking advantage of university-provided counseling services, speaking to your coach, and investing in connecting with your teammates will ease you through this period of emotional transition.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:16pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">New Team, New Family<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">This being said, you were given a place on this new team, by your new coach, for a reason. Don&rsquo;t let that slip away from you those first few months.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Coaches seek out players that are not only gifted in their physical abilities on the field, but they also seek out players that will naturally fit on their team.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Chances are, if you&rsquo;ve been recruited by your current coach, or were welcomed by a coach you reached out to, you belong on your new team. They know it, and you will learn it. Just give it time.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:16pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Focus Is Priority<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Bonding with your teammates is always important, but losing sight of your academic pathway is easily done during a time of transition.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">It can be so easy to forget about a short paper due next week, or to neglect to review your notes for that professor who favors pop quizzes.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">It&rsquo;s easy to want to substitute academic prep for more workout time, but it&rsquo;s important that you don&rsquo;t. Stay focused and utilize your new school&rsquo;s tutoring resources to help you adjust to the workload.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Related Post: <\\/span><\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/vixory.com\\/blog\\/How%20To%20Keep%20Your%20Grades%20In%20Check%20Before%20College%20Transfer,%20Vixory%20Answers\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration:none\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><u>How To Keep Your Grades In Check Before College Transfer, Vixory Answers&nbsp;<\\/u><\\/span><\\/span><\\/a><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<h2><span style=\\\"font-size:17pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Join Vixory Today&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/h2>\\n\\n<h2><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Vixory is here to connect student-athletes with college recruiters and coaches that will lead them toward their future career. We care 