"https:\\/\\/vixory.com\\/registration\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration:none\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><u>register today.&nbsp;<\\/u><\\/span><\\/span><\\/a><\\/h2>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"is_featured\":false}'),(137,'94d4a79c-8324-480d-bcc9-f22fbbf447c1',1,'Update','App\\Models\\BlogPost',9,'App\\Models\\BlogPost',9,'App\\Models\\BlogPost',9,'','finished','','2021-11-08 22:31:00','2021-11-08 22:31:00','{\"content\":\"<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#000000\\\">Investing in the opportunity to be a student-athlete requires commitment and focus. This is because attending a university as an athlete is equivalent to having a full-time job. The field becomes your office, and your teammates are your coworkers.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#000000\\\">Every now and then the environment in the office isn&rsquo;t the right fit, or the coach sees more potential for the student in another department. This is where the student- athlete college transfer process comes into play.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#000000\\\">The transfer process can be long and tedious if not attended to correctly. Vixory understands this and works hard to provide clarity support during this time. In today&rsquo;s blog, Vixory will highlight a few key elements to keep in mind when considering beginning the college transfer process.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p><br \\/>\\n&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:16pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#000000\\\">Wait If You Aren&rsquo;t Sure<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#000000\\\">It&rsquo;s a big decision to decide to move on from a school you&rsquo;ve signed to. Careful consideration is recommended when you decide to tell your coach you plan on moving on, as well as taking the time to consider any financial consequences that could occur.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#000000\\\">Beginning the college transfer process before you are ready can potentially become detrimental to current financial aid you might be receiving, or future aid that can be awarded.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#000000\\\">Checking with financial aid, the registrar, and your advisor first, and notifying them you&rsquo;re considering a transfer is preferred.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#000000\\\">They will have access to resources you will need, and can confirm how your aid will be affected at the school you currently attend.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#000000\\\">Having a school that is interested in signing you on, as well as carefully weighing all of your odds first, before making a decision will help you in the long run.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:16pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#000000\\\">Follow The NCAA Transfer Rules<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#000000\\\">Believe it or not, there are actual rules associated with the division of school you attend, your personal sport, and the level of aid you receive as a student-athlete.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#000000\\\">The NCAA has provided a special <\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.ncaa.org\\/student-athletes\\/current\\/transfer-terms\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration:none\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#1155cc\\\"><u>rule book<\\/u><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/a><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#000000\\\"> to follow when engaging in the college transfer process.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#000000\\\">Becoming well-versed in these rules and regulations as you begin your journey will help you stay eligible to be an NCAA registered athlete, and will protect your team during the season. Having ineligible players on a team will definitely jeopardize your team&rsquo;s eligibility to compete.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#000000\\\">Related Post: <\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/vixory.com\\/blog\\/What%20NCAA%20Transfer%20Rule%20Changes%20Mean%20for%20You\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration:none\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#1155cc\\\"><u>What NCAA Transfer Rule Changes Mean For You<\\/u><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/a><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:16pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#000000\\\">You Are No Longer Required To Sit Out During Transfer<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#000000\\\">In previous years it was important to be aware that certain Division I student-athletes and sports require one year of absence from playing after a transfer.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#000000\\\">This term was called &lsquo;redshirting&rsquo;. It exists to allow both for proper adjustment time for the new player, as well as assurance of fairness for game strategy between the universities the student is transferring between.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#000000\\\">Per the new NCAA rules, &lsquo;redshirting&rsquo; is no longer required to play once an NCAA sanctioned transfer occurs. Sport specific rules should still be reviewed, and contacting an NCAA official to verify your transfer is set to go is still recommended.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p><br \\/>\\n&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<h2><span style=\\\"font-size:17pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#0e101a\\\">Let Vixory Guide Your Steps&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/h2>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#000000\\\">Vixory is here to help you launch into your