an><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">It&rsquo;s so important to remember that your mental health is your biggest asset as a student-athlete. Your mindset is what will set you apart from other athletes.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Exercising your mental endurance is just as important as your physical endurance. So establishing mental boundaries, and mental support the same way you do for physical workouts is key.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Take advantage of your onsite counseling services, even in off-season--the door to the counseling office is open. Open up with your friends and ask for help if you feel down. Call your family.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">All of these small acts of personal service will help you build mental endurance as you balance school with athletics.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br \\/>\\r\\n<br \\/>\\r\\n<br \\/>\\r\\n&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:17pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Register For Vixory Today!<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">At Vixory we care about student athletes and will work to provide as smooth a transfer process as possible. If you&rsquo;re a transferring student-athlete, or simply want to keep up with the community, sign up with us today! We&rsquo;re looking forward to connecting with you!<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"is_featured\":false}'),(154,'95618ec3-cea1-476d-b27e-e853fb21c4f6',1,'Update','App\\Models\\BlogPost',10,'App\\Models\\BlogPost',10,'App\\Models\\BlogPost',10,'','finished','','2022-01-17 23:33:15','2022-01-17 23:33:15','{\"content\":\"<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">So, you&rsquo;ve finished the lengthy process of reviewing your NCAA transfer rule subset specific to your sport, completed the appropriate paperwork between both institutions, and now you&rsquo;re at your new school.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:16pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Now What?<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Every athlete who has completed a college transfer has had this internal feeling as they step onto their new court or field. Luckily, Vixory understands this feeling and has some tips in today&rsquo;s blog on a few things to expect after completing your college transfer.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:16pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Expect An Adjustment Period <\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">A university&rsquo;s athletic community is tightly knit.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Time spent traveling to games and tournaments paired with countless hours spent on team practice, personal workouts, and group workouts creates an unparalleled bonding experience.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">The team is your family, and until you graduate, your university&rsquo;s athletic program is your home. It&rsquo;s okay to have a period of &lsquo;displacement&rsquo; as you adjust to your new athletic family. Many players face low-level depression, loneliness, and stress when adjusting to a transfer.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Taking advantage of university-provided counseling services, speaking to your coach, and investing in connecting with your teammates will ease you through this period of emotional transition.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:16pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">New Team, New Family<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">This being said, you were given a place on this new team, by your new coach, for a reason. Don&rsquo;t let that slip away from you those first few months.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Coaches seek out players that are not only gifted in their physical abilities on the field, but they also seek out players that will naturally fit on their team.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Chances are, if you&rsquo;ve been recruited by your current coach, or were welcomed by a coach you reached out to, you belong on your new team. They know it, and you will learn it. Just give it time.<\\/span>