11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Investing in the opportunity to be a student-athlete requires commitment and focus. This is because attending a university as an athlete is equivalent to having a full-time job. The field becomes your office, and your teammates are your coworkers.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Every now and then the environment in the office isn&rsquo;t the right fit, or the coach sees more potential for the student in another department. This is where the student- athlete college transfer process comes into play.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">The transfer process can be long and tedious if not attended to correctly. Vixory understands this and works hard to provide clarity support during this time. In today&rsquo;s blog, Vixory will highlight a few key elements to keep in mind when considering beginning the college transfer process.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p><br \\/>\\n&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:16pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Wait If You Aren&rsquo;t Sure<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">It&rsquo;s a big decision to decide to move on from a school you&rsquo;ve signed to. Careful consideration is recommended when you decide to tell your coach you plan on moving on, as well as taking the time to consider any financial consequences that could occur.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Beginning the college transfer process before you are ready can potentially become detrimental to current financial aid you might be receiving, or future aid that can be awarded.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Checking with financial aid, the registrar, and your advisor first, and notifying them you&rsquo;re considering a transfer is preferred.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">They will have access to resources you will need, and can confirm how your aid will be affected at the school you currently attend.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Having a school that is interested in signing you on, as well as carefully weighing all of your odds first, before making a decision will help you in the long run.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:16pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Follow The NCAA Transfer Rules<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Believe it or not, there are actual rules associated with the division of school you attend, your personal sport, and the level of aid you receive as a student-athlete.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">The NCAA has provided a special <\\/span><\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.ncaa.org\\/student-athletes\\/current\\/transfer-terms\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration:none\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><u>rule book<\\/u><\\/span><\\/span><\\/a><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"> to follow when engaging in the college transfer process.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Becoming well-versed in these rules and regulations as you begin your journey will help you stay eligible to be an NCAA registered athlete, and will protect your team during the season. Having ineligible players on a team will definitely jeopardize your team&rsquo;s eligibility to compete.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Related Post: <\\/span><\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/vixory.com\\/blog\\/What%20NCAA%20Transfer%20Rule%20Changes%20Mean%20for%20You\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration:none\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><u>What NCAA Transfer Rule Changes Mean For You<\\/u><\\/span><\\/span><\\/a><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:16pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">You Are No Longer Required To Sit Out During Transfer<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">In previous years it was important to be aware that certain Division I student-athletes and sports require one year of absence from playing after a transfer.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">This term was called &lsquo;redshirting&rsquo;. It exists to allow both for proper adjustment time for the new player, as well as assurance of fairness for game strategy between the universities the student is transferring between.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Per the new NCAA rules, &lsquo;redshirting&rsquo; is no longer required to play once an NCAA sanctioned transfer occurs. Sport specific rules should still be reviewed, and contacting an NCAA official to verify your transfer is set to go is still recommended.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p><br \\/>\\n&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<h2><span style=\\\"font-size:17pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Let Vixory Guide Your Steps&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/h2>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Vixory is here to help you launch into your future career. We create connection opportunities for athletes and universities around the nation. Our goal is to create an informed and thriving student-athlete community. If you have any questions on athletic transfer we&rsquo;d love to hear from you. Start the <\\/span><\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/vixory.com\\/registration\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration:none\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><u>registration process<\\/u><\\/span><\\/span><\\/a><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"> and learn more about why Vixory is the perfect platform for you.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\",\"is_featured\":0}','{\"content\":\"<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Investing in the opportunity to be a student-athlete requires commitment and focus. This is because attending a university as an athlete is equivalent to having a full-time job. The field becomes your office, and your teammates are your coworkers.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Every now and then the environment in the office isn&rsquo;t the right fit, or the coach sees more potential for the student in another department. This is where the student- athlete college transfer process comes into play.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">The transfer process can be long and tedious if not attended to correctly. Vixory understands this and works hard to provide clarity support during this time. In today&rsquo;s blog, Vixory will highlight a few key elements to keep in mind when considering beginning the college transfer process.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br \\/>\\r\\n&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:16pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Wait If You Aren&rsquo;t Sure<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">It&rsquo;s a big decision to decide to move on from a school you&rsquo;ve signed to. Careful consideration is recommended when you decide to tell your coach you plan on moving on, as well as taking the time to consider any financial consequences that could occur.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Beginning the college transfer process before you are ready can potentially become detrimental to current financial aid you might be receiving, or future aid that can be awarded.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Checking with financial aid, the registrar, and your advisor first, and notifying them you&rsquo;re considering a transfer is preferred.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">They will have access to resources you will need, and can confirm how your aid will be affected at the school you currently attend.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Having a school that is interested in signing you on, as well as carefully weighing all of your odds first, before making a decision will help you in the long run.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:16pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Follow The NCAA Transfer Rules<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Believe it or not, there are actual rules associated with the division of school you attend, your personal sport, and the level of aid you receive as a student-athlete.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">The NCAA has provided a special <\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.ncaa.org\\/student-athletes\\/current\\/transfer-terms\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration:none\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><u>rule book<\\/u><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/a><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"> to follow when engaging in the college transfer process.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Becoming well-versed in these rules and regulations as you begin your journey will help you stay eligible to be an NCAA registered athlete, and will protect your team during the season. Having ineligible players on a team will definitely jeopardize your team&rsquo;s eligibility to compete.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Related Post: <\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/vixory.com\\/blog\\/What%20NCAA%20Transfer%20Rule%20Changes%20Mean%20for%20You\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration:none\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><u>What NCAA Transfer Rule Changes Mean For You<\\/u><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:16pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">You Are No Longer Required To Sit Out During Transfer<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">In previous years it was important to be aware that certain Division I student-athletes and sports require one year of absence from playing after a transfer.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">This term was called &lsquo;redshirting&rsquo;. It exists to allow both for proper adjustment time for the new player, as well as assurance of fairness for game strategy between the universities the student is transferring between.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Per the new NCAA rules, &lsquo;redshirting&rsquo; is no longer required to play once an NCAA sanctioned transfer occurs. Sport specific rules should still be reviewed, and contacting an NCAA official to verify your transfer is set to go is still recommended.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br \\/>\\r\\n&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:17pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Let Vixory Guide Your Steps&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Vixory is here to help you launch into your future career. We create connection opportunities for athletes and universities around the nation. Our goal is to create an informed and thriving student-athlete community. If you have any questions on athletic transfer we&rsquo;d love to hear from you. Start the <\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/vixory.com\\/registration\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration:none\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><u>registration process<\\/u><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/a><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"> and learn more about why Vixory is the perfect platform for you.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\",\"is_featured\":false}'),(156,'95618f18-6d3f-46c1-b093-9b8e7ce672ee',1,'Update','App\\Models\\BlogPost',8,'App\\Models\\BlogPost',8,'App\\Models\\BlogPost',8,'','finished','','2022-01-17 23:34:11','2022-01-17 23:34:11','{\"content\":\"<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Student athletes are experts at understanding the meaning of the word, &lsquo;busy&rsquo;. Most collegiate athletes are up at early hours of the morning for practice before class, followed by time spent in their studies, and ending with more practice in off season or games during season in the evenings.&nbsp; In today&rsquo;s blog, Vixory will cover the importance of finding balance in the world of being a student athlete.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:16pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Maintain Realistic Expectations For Yourself<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Required weekly exercise quotas to maintain strength and endurance fill the time of a student athlete, along with additional team involvement and academic progress.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">An important mentality to keep when entering into the arena of college athletics is the mentality of resilience and realistic expectations. Simply put, as you are adjusting it&rsquo;s important not to get ahead of yourself and the moment.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">It is extremely exciting to begin the journey of transfer, and to begin at a new school with a new team. However, it&#39;s important to take each day as it comes.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">First focus on learning your daily routine and setting your weekly schedule with balancing academics and athletics. Then focus on adding in time for yourself as you find that balance.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Add in social time to spend with new found friends and calling family members as well. However, remember that each day is unique and if you need to sparse your expectations for extracurriculars throughout the week, that is okay.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Becoming a student athlete is a fulltime job, so it&rsquo;s important to&nbsp; understand that the entire journey is a learning process.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:13pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Start The Day With Simple Goals<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">One way to manage your expectations&nbsp; appropriately is to begin each day with the simple goals of:<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<ul>\\n\\t<li style=\\\"list-style-type:disc\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Personal Hygiene<\\/span><\\/span><\\/li>\\n\\t<li style=\\\"list-style-type:disc\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Practice<\\/span><\\/span><\\/li>\\n\\t<li style=\\\"list-style-type:disc\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Performance<\\/span><\\/span><\\/li>\\n\\t<li style=\\\"list-style-type:disc\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Productivity in school work<\\/span><\\/span><\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Learning how these different bullet points interact with each other throughout the day is perfectly okay, but it&rsquo;s important to visit each of them to stay on track.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:13pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Media Management&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Streaming services, smart phones, and gaming are amazing outlets for entertainment and personal expression. However, too much screen time not only affects focusing abilities, but can also interfere with sleep.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Stimulating the brain just before bed can result in sleep coming later than intended which can affect your performance. It&rsquo;s important to keep your media time managed within earlier hours of the day, or unplugging about an hour before bed to allow your mind and body to relax from the stimulation of consuming.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:16pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Schedule Management&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">A busy person&rsquo;s path to peace is in schedule management. Learning what consistent timeblocks you are working with for finishing schoolwork, taking personal time, and performing while in uniform is the ultimate method for maintaining the expectations you, and others, have set for yourself.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Whether you utlize the calendar and task management services on your smart phone, or invest in a management service app, it&rsquo;s important to find the method most usable to you.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<h2><span style=\\\"font-size:17pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Join Vixory Today&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/h2>\\n\\n<h2><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Vixory is here to connect student athletes with college recruiters and coaches that will lead them toward their future career. We care about our student athletes that register with us, and work to provide them an optimal experience. If you are interested in athletic transfer, we&rsquo;d love to hear from you! Follow our link to <\\/span><\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/vixory.com\\/registration\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration:none\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><u>register today.&nbsp;<\\/u><\\/span><\\/span><\\/a><\\/h2>\\n\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"is_featured\":0}','{\"content\":\"<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Student athletes are experts at understanding the meaning of the word, &lsquo;busy&rsquo;. Most collegiate athletes are up at early hours of the morning for practice before class, followed by time spent in their studies, and ending with more practice in off season or games during season in the evenings.&nbsp; In today&rsquo;s blog, Vixory will cover the importance of finding balance in the world of being a student athlete.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:16pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Maintain Realistic Expectations For Yourself<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Required weekly exercise quotas to maintain strength and endu