derstanding is that coaches and recruiters will cycle through the sport of their interest during the season. Fall sports will see recruiters during the fall, etc.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/h2>\\n\\n<h2><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:16pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">How Do I Know I&rsquo;m Being Recruited?<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/h2>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">The recruiting process can sometimes be a bit confusing. Vixory understands this, which is why below we&rsquo;ve covered an outline of the process to keep you informed as you move forward.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<ul>\\n\\t<li style=\\\"list-style-type:disc\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">You will be told<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span>\\n\\n\\t<ul>\\n\\t\\t<li style=\\\"list-style-type:circle\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">According to the NCAA rules, anytime a college coach speaks to you about sports&mdash;other than a hello&mdash; it&rsquo;s considered a <\\/span><\\/span><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><strong>contact. <\\/strong><\\/span><\\/span><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Coaches making contact with players signal their interest in starting the recruiting process.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/li>\\n\\t<\\/ul>\\n\\t<\\/li>\\n\\t<li style=\\\"list-style-type:disc\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">You will be evaluated<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span>\\n\\t<ul>\\n\\t\\t<li style=\\\"list-style-type:circle\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Coaches attending your games are evaluating how you play and how your style will fit their team. When a coach is watching your game, know that it is an evaluation that could lead to more, so play your best!<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/li>\\n\\t<\\/ul>\\n\\t<\\/li>\\n\\t<li style=\\\"list-style-type:disc\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">You will be invited for an official visit (DI and D2)<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span>\\n\\t<ul>\\n\\t\\t<li style=\\\"list-style-type:circle\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Official visits are college visits paid for by the university. These visits include roundtrip travel expenses, three meals a day while on-site, and tickets for you and your family for up to three sporting events. Being invited for an official visit occurs after a successful player evaluation. If a coach is impressed by your evaluation, they will likely invite you for an official visit.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/li>\\n\\t<\\/ul>\\n\\t<\\/li>\\n\\t<li style=\\\"list-style-type:disc\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">You will receive an official offer and be asked for a verbal commitment&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span>\\n\\t<ul>\\n\\t\\t<li style=\\\"list-style-type:circle\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">A verbal commitment is when a player verbally agrees to attend a university for athletics. These commitments are non-binding but often lead to signings, as they signal to the coach the player is serious about their interest. If you are presented with the opportunity to give a verbal, it is likely you will have the opportunity to follow up and sign your letter of intent.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/li>\\n\\t<\\/ul>\\n\\t<\\/li>\\n\\t<li style=\\\"list-style-type:disc\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">You will sign a letter of intent<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span>\\n\\t<ul>\\n\\t\\t<li style=\\\"list-style-type:circle\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Letters of intent are issued through the NCAA, and are the official binding contract that solidifies a player&rsquo;s spot on the team and in the school for the next year. If you are presented one, chances are you know that you are attending college and playing athletics at the school you are signing for.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/li>\\n\\t<\\/ul>\\n\\t<\\/li>\\n<\\/ul>\\n\\n<h2><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:16pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Which Schools Are Required To Officially Recruit Through The NCAA?<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/h2>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Believe it or not, not all schools follow the same recruiting process. Division I and Division II athletics must follow a similar path due to the prestigious nature of the institutions. Signings of intent are an example. DI and DII schools must present a player with an intent form in order to contract them to the team. DIII schools, on the other hand, are allowed to present a celebratory signing form as more of a symbolic measure.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\n\\n<h2><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:17pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Register For Vixory Today!<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/h2>\\n\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ff