nsure a smooth transfer process.\",\"is_featured\":false,\"content\":\"<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#ffffff\\\">The collegiate athletic transfer process can feel daunting for any potential DI-DIII, JUCO, or NAIA transferring student-athlete. How do you ensure a transfer occurs? What can you do to simplify the process? Our team at Vixory can certainly help. In today&rsquo;s blog, Vixory discusses three simple steps that any collegiate student-athlete can take to ensure their transfer process moves smoothly.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:17pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#ffffff\\\">Gather the Right Information<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#ffffff\\\">The first step to take that helps ensure your transfer is simple: gather all of the important information required to make this decision! Deciding to transfer can be difficult, so before you do anything, make sure that you are well informed and understand what you can expect as you move forward through the process. If you&rsquo;re a student-athlete that desires a transfer, here are some things to consider first:&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol>\\r\\n\\t<li style=\\\"list-style-type:decimal\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#ffffff\\\">What are your dream schools?<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li style=\\\"list-style-type:decimal\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"fon