fferences. If you are transferring from a DIII, JUCO, or NAIA school, first decide what division of college sports you would like to move into, and research their specific transfer processes.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:17pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">Enter the Transfer Portal&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">Once you feel equipped with the right information, you can begin the process by entering into the <\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/s3.amazonaws.com\\/static.ncaa.org\\/static\\/champion\\/what-the-ncaa-transfer-portal-is\\/index.html\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration:none\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><u><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">NCAA transfer portal<\\/span><\\/u><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/a><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">. To do this, you will need to inform your current coach and school administrator of your intent to transfer, which will prompt their compliance team to submit your name into the transfer portal within two business days. If you have a good relationship with your current school&rsquo;s coaching staff, these conversations can be hard to initiate. Transferring athletes will typically thank their coaches for the opportunity to represent the school and compete on its behalf and then describe the reasons why they feel a transfer is in their best interest. Once your current school is informed and your name is added to the transfer portal, you can have complete contact with other schools about the possibility of a transfer.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><strong><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">Related Post:<\\/span><\\/strong><\\/span><\\/span><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\"> <\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/vixory.com\\/blog\\/What%20Are%20Myths%20Associated%20With%20College%20T\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration:none\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><u><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">What Are the Myths Associated With College Transfers?<\\/span><\\/u><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:17pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">Communicate with Schools<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">With your name entered into the NCAA transfer portal, school officials and coaches are allowed to contact you with interest in recruiting you to their teams. During this phase of the process, you can help ensure a smooth transfer by maintaining great contact with all coaches who have reached out to you. Also, be sure to personally reach out to the schools you are most interested in, even if they haven&rsquo;t contacted you first! You must ask the right questions and be transparent with the schools you are interested in, that way, you can be confident that your next school meets your criteria and sets you up for a win in the classroom and on the field. As a prospective transfer, you have essentially been given a second chance in the recruiting process, so take full advantage of it!<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:17pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">Vixory Makes the Transfer Process Easier<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">If you are a collegiate student-athlete interested in transferring to a different school, you can help expedite the process by joining Vixory! With our state-of-the-art platform, you can post highlight videos, stats, and other information that is kept anonymous for other coaches to review. Once you&rsquo;ve entered the transfer portal, you are one step ahead in finding the right school to continue your athletic career! To learn more about Vixory and how we aid all transferring athletes, <\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/vixory.com\\/\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration:none\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><u><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">contact us<\\/span><\\/u><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/a><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\"> online today!<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"is_featured\":false}'),(201,'96509d1a-6fc7-4e27-9517-4ace19b7760b',1,'Create','App\\Models\\BlogPost',21,'App\\Models\\BlogPost',21,'App\\Models\\BlogPost',21,'','finished','','2022-05-16 19:36:13','2022-05-16 19:36:13',NULL,'{\"title\":\"What Are The Different Athletic Scholarships Available to Student-Athletes?\",\"short_description\":\"In today\'s blog, Vixory explains the different types of athletic scholarships available for student-athletes.\",\"is_featured\":false,\"content\":\"<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Receiving an athletic scholarship is a dream come true. For many student-athletes, attending a university through a scholarship is the only way they can pursue a college education or continue competing in their chosen sport. With several different types of athletic scholarships offered by recruiters and coaches, it can feel overwhelming. In today&#39;s blog, the team at Vixory is here to help by explaining the different types of athletic scholarships offered by universities.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span>&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:17pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Full-ride Athletic Scholarships<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">For many high school athletes, a full-ride athletic scholarship is a dream. As the name implies, this type of athletic scholarship covers the entire tuition cost for an incoming athlete.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Even better, some universities offer a more comprehensive version of a full-ride scholarship, which includes the entirety of necessary costs for a student-athlete&#39;s college experience (tuition, books, housing, and supplies). As full-ride scholarships are rare, the athlete must be among the best in their respective sport and be academically eligible based on the institution&#39;s standards.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Full-ride athletic scholarships can be given to any qualifying athlete that a coach is looking to sign, as long as the university provides the coach with enough budget for scholarships. Full-ride scholarship options are only available for sports that bring in revenue for most schools.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:17pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Partial Athletic Scholarship<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">For athletes who do not play big-revenue sports or would like to attend a smaller university, partial athletic scholarships are great options! While some coaches can offer full-ride scholarships, others are given a specific budget in scholarship money divided among their recruiting class.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">As the scholarship amounts are separated, while they may not cover the entire cost of college education, they are still a great way to make the university experience affordable!<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><strong>Related Post:<\\/strong><\\/span><\\/span><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"> <\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/vixory.com\\/blog\\/Vixory%20Explains%20the%20College%20Recruitment%20\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration:none\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><u>Vixory Explains the College Recruitment Process<\\/u><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:17pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Walk-on Opportunities&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">As recruiting classes fill up very quickly, a student-athlete&#39;s first choice in a university may have already allocated their entire scholarship budget for the year. Walk-on opportunities are a great way to join the team you want and potentially earn a future scholarship opportunity at your top school. Here are the two different types of walk-on opportunities:&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:13pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><strong>Recruited Walk-ons<\\/strong><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">This type of walk-on opportunity means that a coach is interested in the athlete but without financial assistance offered. However, the athlete can always earn their financial aid through an athletic scholarship while competing for a spot on the team as a recruited walk-on.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:13pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><strong>Unrecruited Walk-ons<\\/strong><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Unrecruited walk-ons qualify academically for admission into the university and attempt to join the team through an open try-out. In most cases, it&#39;s necessary to communicate with the college coach and ensure that a try-out opportunity is available.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:17pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Find New Athletic Scholarships with Vixory<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">If you are a collegiate student-athlete and interested in new athletic scholarship opportunities at different schools, Vixory can help! We offer a free-to-use platform that anonymously connects student-athletes with college recruiters and coaches, allowing you to showcase your highlights, stats, and other information. To learn more about Vixory and how we help athletes land at their dream schools, <\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/vixory.com\\/\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration:none\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><u>contact us<\\/u><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/a><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"> online today!<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"blog_category_id\":3,\"meta_title\":\"What Are The Different Athletic Scholarships Available to Student-Athletes? Vixory Answers\",\"meta_description\":\"In today\'s blog, Vixory explains the different types of athletic scholarships available for student-athletes.\",\"featured_image\":\"VpioURyKW6Xh5OvsfOpXDY3JxaVrdL3olVUHnSEF.jpg\",\"updated_at\":\"2022-05-16T19:36:13.000000Z\",\"created_at\":\"2022-05-16T19:36:13.000000Z\",\"id\":21}'),(202,'9696ba7c-a0d1-4969-9c1c-d4735d1cc187',2,'Update','App\\Models\\College',1966,'App\\Models\\College',1966,'App\\Models\\College',1966,'','finished','','2022-06-20 16:06:19','2022-06-20 16:06:19','{\"city\":null,\"state_code\":null,\"type\":null,\"division\":null,\"domain\":null}','{\"city\":\"Senatobia\",\"state_code\":24,\"type\":1,\"division\":0,\"domain\":\"https:\\/\\/www.northwestms.edu\\/\"}'),(203,'96974623-945d-41cf-931a-3934953c2318',1,'Create','App\\Models\\BlogPost',22,'App\\Models\\BlogPost',22,'App\\Models\\BlogPost',22,'','finished','','2022-06-20 22:36:49','2022-06-20 22:36:49',NULL,'{\"title\":\"Top Study Aid Services For Student-Athletes\",\"short_description\":\"Accelerate your learning with the help of these top study aid services, compiled by the team at Vixory.\",\"is_featured\":false,\"content\":\"<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Student-athletes time in a week is precious, as they juggle workouts, team practices, and athletic competition with classes and academic study. A research study conducted by a South Dakota State University student found that 37% of the surveyed student-athletes spend 20+ hours per week fulfilling their athletic commitments. 49% of student-athletes devote 10-15 hours a week to academic coursework.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Needless to say, an athlete&#39;s time is a hot commodity.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Student-athletes need to stay ahead of the game regarding academic work. Many of them frequently study in-between workouts and games. Our team at Vixory has compiled information on several different study aid services used across the country! In today&#39;s blog, check out these resources and see if any are a right fit for you!&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:17pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Best Study Aid Platforms<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Here are some of the best study aid platforms available for collegiate student-athletes today:&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:13pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><strong>Chegg<\\/strong><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.chegg.com\\/\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration:none\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><u>Chegg<\\/u><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/a><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"> has evolved from a famous textbook rental supplier into a full-scale academic resource center for college students. Not only can you rent textbooks in just a few clicks, but you can also receive homework assistance 24\\/7 from Chegg&#39;s team of academic professionals. Chegg also offers exam preparation and practice for students who want to make sure they ace that upcoming test.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:13pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><strong>Khan Academy<\\/strong><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\">Started in 2008 by Salman Khan, <\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.khanacademy.org\\/\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration:none\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><u>Khan Academy<\\/u><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/a><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"> has become a popular resource for students in any grade, at any age. The organization has expanded to provide free classes that span many subjects, from Pre-K to college-level. Khan Academy is a fantastic study aid platform for student-athletes as classes are 100% free and personalized for students to practice at their own pace and accelerate their learning.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:13pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><strong>Grammarly<\\/strong><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/grammarly.com\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration:none\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><u>Grammarly<\\/u><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/a><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"> is hands down one of the most popular writing assistants available today. The Grammarly writing assistant analyzes your writing and offers grammatical and spelling suggestions to improve your written work using cutting-edge technology. Perfect for on-the-go student-athletes, this writing assistant tool can take your final papers or presentations to the next level, free of cost. Grammarly can conveniently be used as a plug-in extension on Google Chrome, Safari, Microsoft Edge, or any browser you prefer, allowing you to receive real-time feedback as you finish up your writing assignments on Google Docs or a Microsoft Word document.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n