ferring Colleges\",\"short_description\":\"In today\\u2019s blog, our team at Vixory has provided answers to the most frequently asked questions coming from student-athletes who are interested in a college transfer.\",\"is_featured\":false,\"content\":\"<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#ffffff\\\">If you are considering moving on from your current university, you probably have many questions! In today&rsquo;s blog, our team at Vixory has provided answers to the most frequently asked questions coming from student-athletes who are interested in a college transfer.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:17pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#ffffff\\\">Should I Transfer Colleges, or Not?<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#ffffff\\\">Transferring from your current university or community college is a big decision, which should not be taken lightly. First, consider the reasons why you could see yourself moving on to a different school, and why you might prefer to stay. Are you pursuing the degree of your choice? Are you able to athletically compete at your desired level? Are you happy with your team dynamic and coaching staff? These are some of the many questions you should be asking yourself.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#ffffff\\\">To learn more, check out this blog that outlines other <\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/