\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">It is best to speak with your school&rsquo;s financial aid office about your consideration of transfer, as you will need to consider how your financial aid package could be affected by your transfer. With all of these variables in consideration, the spring and summer seasons are a popular time of year for athletes to make preparations for transfer.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:17pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">Will My Credits Transfer?<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">Academic credit transfers solely depend on regulations from your current institution, and the university you are transferring to If you are an athlete going from a JUCO to a Division I-III school, most (if not all) credits should transfer without issue, as a majority of these credits will be deemed general prerequisites.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">If you go from one four-year university to another (especially if one institution is a private school), then you may encounter certain credits not transferring over. Be sure to communicate with both schools and make a game plan for how your completed credits may transfer, or which classes you will need to enroll in once you arrive at your new school.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:17pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">How Do I Select the Right College?&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">Selecting the right new college is based on your needs and wants in a university. Consider the questions mentioned at the beginning of this blog, and organize your thoughts about all prospective new schools.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">You will also want to stay in communication with new coaches and scouts that are interested in making you a part of their team. The number of scholarships you are eligible to receive, geographical location, and available degrees are also important factors to consider.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:17pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">Vixory Helps You Transfer&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">The <\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/vixory.com\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration:none\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><u><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">Vixory platform<\\/span><\\/u><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/a><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\"> makes it easy to seek out a transfer, even before entering the transfer portal. Vixory also specializes in giving JUCO players the right opportunities to be looked at by new coaches and recruiters at higher levels of competition.&nbsp; Sign up today for a free Vixory account to begin your journey to your dream school! <\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\",\"is_featured\":false}'),(214,'96c13faf-b78f-49e3-a237-f4098986674c',1,'Create','App\\Models\\BlogPost',25,'App\\Models\\BlogPost',25,'App\\Models\\BlogPost',25,'','finished','','2022-07-11 19:23:33','2022-07-11 19:23:33',NULL,'{\"title\":\"When is it Too Late to Transfer Colleges? Vixory Explains.\",\"short_description\":\"Vixory explains when it is too late to transfer colleges, and provides guidance on how to navigate the different timelines and obstacles that pertain to your college transfer.\",\"is_featured\":false,\"content\":\"<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">Collegiate student-athletes who are unhappy with their current school or team could easily find themselves wondering, &ldquo;Is it too late to transfer colleges?&rdquo;&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">In today&rsquo;s blog, Vixory answers this question and provides guidance on how to navigate the different timelines and obstacles that pertain to your college transfer.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:17pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">Is It Ever Too Late to Transfer Colleges?<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">To answer this question, you first need to understand the &ldquo;five-year clock&rdquo; concept. Once enrolled into a university, a student-athlete has five years of eligibility, in which they can compete in their sport for four seasons.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">Under the new NCAA transfer portal rules, as long as an athlete is within the five-year clock and is academically eligible, they are allowed a one-time transfer to a new school and can begin competing right away.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:17pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">Timeline for DI-DIII Student-Athlete Transfers<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">For student-athletes who are transferring within DI-DIII divisions, they will need to inform their current school with a Notification of Transfer. Below, you will find guidelines and dates that athletes and institutions will need follow during this process:<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li style=\\\"list-style-type:disc\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">Fall and winter sports: athletes should provide written notice before May 1st&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li style=\\\"list-style-type:disc\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">Spring sports: athletes should provide written notice before July 1st<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li style=\\\"list-style-type:disc\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">Colleges have two business days to enter your name into the transfer portal<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">Students who want to transfer will need to ensure they meet their desired school&rsquo;s (and the conference the school is found in) guidelines for eligibility and have collected all necessary documentation regarding academics and financial aid. After giving your notification of transfer by the summertime deadline, all other deadlines will be dependent on the new school and team you pursue.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:17pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">Timeline for JuCo Student-Athlete Transfers<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">Transferring student-athletes who are looking to make the switch from their JuCo program to a different JuCo follow a similar process as that of DI-DIII transfers. However, players who are looking to go from JUCO to DI will have to follow a unique path.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">The easiest way to transfer from JUCO to DI is to simply graduate from your current JuCo after obtaining your associate&rsquo;s degree. If you are interested in leaving your JuCo early, it is certainly possible, only as long as you meet certain academic criteria.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">First, the transferring student-athlete must register with the NCAA Eligibility Center. If you meet their guidelines and requirements, you will be considered as an academic qualifier, and you will be set to join your next school.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">For some students, the NCAA deems them an academic non-qualifier, which means there will be a few extra hurdles to jump through. Review your academic records against <\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/education.seattlepi.com\\/junior-college-transfer-rules-2346.html\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration:none\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><u><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">these guidelines<\\/span><\\/u><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/a><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\"> to see how you match up, as well as stay in contact with representatives from the NCAA and your current school.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:17pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">Make Transferring Colleges Simple with Vixory&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/vixory.com\\/\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration:none\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><u><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">Vixory<\\/span><\\/u><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/a><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\"> gives you an edge on your competition by empowering you to start prospecting for your dream school and team, all before your notification of transfer is written. By posting highlights and statistics that can only be viewed by coaches and recruiters from outside of your current school, you can feel out other options before making the big jump. If you are interested in this advantage, <\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/vixory.com\\/registration\\\" style=\\\"text-decoration:none\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><u><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\">sign up today<\\/span><\\/u><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/a><span style=\\\"color:#ffffff\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"background-color:#000000\\\"> for a free account and begin your journey to your next school!<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\",\"blog_category_id\":2,\"meta_title\":\"Is it Too Late to Transfer Colleges? Vixory Explains.\",\"meta_description\":\"Vixory explains when it is too late to transfer colleges, and provides guidance on how to navigate the different timelines and obstacles that pertain to your college transfer.\",\"featured_image\":\"JsG3mf7mwRv9k6U1CkWEFGdBcg39oI9egwD3lGXg.jpg\",\"updated_at\":\"2022-07-11T19:23:33.000000Z\",\"created_at\":\"2022-07-11T19:23:33.000000Z\",\"id\":25}'),(215,'96c53524-d4ef-4424-9aa5-aaa2be0956e7',2,'Update','App\\User',186,'App\\User',186,'App\\User',186,'','finished','','2022-07-13 18:37:23','2022-07-13 18:37:23','{\"password\":\"$2y$10$\\/k0AyTY2.PI32ANhC20QEOZtmwZAjhVe5UhyLJ981Ag2DHJhwDZTi\",\"show_info\":1}','{\"password\":\"$2y$10$1FcRAIed\\/6GD3w9CnuoxZ.BtVfYNEzar954jOAhlrUP60RrWUMcEy\",\"show_info\":true}'),(216,'96c54401-f143-44d6-96ed-49d75de3249d',230,'Attach','App\\User',230,'Spatie\\Permission\\Models\\Role',12,'Illuminate\\Database\\Eloquent\\Relations\\MorphPivot',NULL,'','finished','','2022-07-13 19:18:57','2022-07-13 19:18:57',NULL,'{\"model_id\":\"230\",\"role_id\":\"12\",\"model_type\":\"App\\\\User\"}');
