d suggestions to assure you are on the right track to success. Our players get recognized by talent scouts and coaches daily.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Related Post: </span></span></span><a href=\"https://vixory.com/blog/How%20Vixory%20Helps%20You%20to%20Transfer%20Schools\" style=\"text-decoration:none\"><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><u>How Vixory Helps You to Transfer Schools</u></span></span></span></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:17pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Diversify Your Portfolio:</span></span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">On the Vixory website, you can upload highlights of your best performances and games to build your portfolio. Become an established player and send off iconic moments to schools that will accelerate your game and allow a smooth transition process.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:17pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Stay in Touch With the Officials of Your Top Institution&nbsp;</span></span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">&nbsp;Coaches and scouts want the best of the best, and they will spend their time and efforts finding what they need most. Build your talents and keep in contact with the officials of your desired school to demonstrate dedication to your craft and persistence. Staying in touch will keep you in their thoughts, and as a skilled player, you are the priority.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:17pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Victory Helps You Focus On Your Endgame&nbsp;</span></span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Find a transfer program that fits your priorities through Vixory. Our team has created a hub where top-tier players can build their online presence to showcase their talents to coaches from the best universities in the nation. Time is essential; you owe it to yourself as a committed player to have a committed team working with you. </span></span></span><a href=\"https://vixory.com/registration\" style=\"text-decoration:none\"><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><u>Get started with Vixory today.&nbsp;</u></span></span></span></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2021-09-02 00:17:55','2022-01-17 23:34:46','Steps to Begin the Athletic transfer process, Vixory','Vixory explains all you need to know about transferring to a different college to start your athletic career as a student-athlete. Read to learn more.',0,'yMV7WiYPF6PAIUvSGuVKTKUBL3o3W6ERFcPlGNo3.png','Vixory explains all you need to know about transferring to a different college to start your athletic career as a student-athlete. Read to learn more.'),(7,'How To Keep Your Grades In Check Before College Transfer, Vixory Answers',2,'<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">The professional sporting industry is filled with hopeful future professionals. Vixory is here to ensure those that utilize our service to transfer into schools that prepare them for their futures are prepared to take on that challenge. In today&rsquo;s blog, we&rsquo;ll discuss our top tips for keeping your grades in check while preparing for college transfer.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:16pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Set Aside Time For Study/Work Review</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">One of the priorities of every student athlete should be setting aside homework time to help manage their grades. Many student athletes go to college on sport scholarships, and these scholarships are often paired with grade requirements that must be met to keep them on the team.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Ignoring your grades is ignoring your future. So how do you manage that pressure along with the expectations as an athlete?&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">You advocate for it. Don&rsquo;t go out with friends after practice, set time aside in your schedule that is specifically designed for homework time. Then stick to that time.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:16pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Utilize Your Current School&rsquo;s Student Resources</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">&nbsp;All schools offer tutoring services, class assistance, and some form of teaching aid per subject matter focus to aid all students learning the material. If you are struggling with a particular subject, and you are a student athlete, reach out to your student resource center.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Many tutors are willing to work with tight schedules by offering virtual tutoring services, virtual work review, and personalized tutoring to the schedule that works best for you. Oftentimes specific universities will also have tutors designated to students with specific needs, such as student athletes.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Talk to your coach and teammates first to see if there is a tutor that is popularly recommended, or even designated to your team. Then follow up with your student resource center for hours available to help you succeed.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:16pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Schedule Management</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Part of the college experience is learning the meaning of the word, &lsquo;balance&rsquo;.&nbsp; Finding balance in college is about understanding priorities and how to manage them.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Schedule management is key when learning how to manage multiple priorities at once. Smart phones offer both calendar services, and scheduling task tools to keep you on track throughout your day.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">For some individuals this means color blocking out their calendar and setting hourly reminders of their tasks needing to be completed. For others it means starting each day with a To Do List of tasks to complete by the end of the day.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Whatever you find that works for you is awesome! Just remember to balance your academic, athletic, and emotional priorities by also allowing time for a bit of self care as well. Use your system to your advantage and pencil in some personal time.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:17pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Let Vixory Guide Your Steps&nbsp;</span></span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Vixory is here to help you launch into your future career. We create connection opportunities for athletes and universities around the nation. Our goal is to create an informed and thriving student athlete community. If you have any questions on athletic transfer we&rsquo;d love to hear from you. Start the </span></span></span><a href=\"https://vixory.com/registration\" style=\"text-decoration:none\"><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><u>registration process</u></span></span></span></a><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"> and learn more about why Vixory is the perfect platform for you.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2021-09-26 05:37:17','2022-01-17 23:34:27','Tips To Keep Your Grades Up by Vixory','Vixory helps students prepare for college transfer by focusing on both their sport of specialization and their grades.',1,'rfLBD0CMbr86xU8GiKvJZdSSBuXv0OHtQp7YS4IH.jpg','Vixory helps students prepare for college transfer by focusing on both their sport of specialization and their grades.'),(8,'Self Care Tips For The Transferring College Athlete, Vixory',2,'<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Student athletes are experts at understanding the meaning of the word, &lsquo;busy&rsquo;. Most collegiate athletes are up at early hours of the morning for practice before class, followed by time spent in their studies, and ending with more practice in off season or games during season in the evenings.&nbsp; In today&rsquo;s blog, Vixory will cover the importance of finding balance in the world of being a student athlete.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:16pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Maintain Realistic Expectations For Yourself</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Required weekly exercise quotas to maintain strength and endurance fill the time of a student athlete, along with additional team involvement and academic progress.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">An important mentality to keep when entering into the arena of college athletics is the mentality of resilience and realistic expectations. Simply put, as you are adjusting it&rsquo;s important not to get ahead of yourself and the moment.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">It is extremely exciting to begin the journey of transfer, and to begin at a new school with a new team. However, it&#39;s important to take each day as it comes.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">First focus on learning your daily routine and setting your weekly schedule with balancing academics and athletics. Then focus on adding in time for yourself as you find that balance.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Add in social time to spend with new found friends and calling family members as well. However, remember that each day is unique and if you need to sparse your expectations for extracurriculars throughout the week, that is okay.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Becoming a student athlete is a fulltime job, so it&rsquo;s important to&nbsp; understand that the entire journey is a learning process.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Start The Day With Simple Goals</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">One way to manage your expectations&nbsp; appropriately is to begin each day with the simple goals of:</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Personal Hygiene</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Practice</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Performance</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"list-style-type:disc\"><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Productivity in school work</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Learning how these different bullet points interact with each other throughout the day is perfectly okay, but it&rsquo;s important to visit each of them to stay on track.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Media Management&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Streaming services, smart phones, and gaming are amazing outlets for entertainment and personal expression. However, too much screen time not only affects focusing abilities, but can also interfere with sleep.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Stimulating the brain just before bed can result in sleep coming later than intended which can affect your performance. It&rsquo;s important to keep your media time managed within earlier hours of the day, or unplugging about an hour before bed to allow your mind and body to relax from the stimulation of consuming.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:16pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Schedule Management&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">A busy person&rsquo;s path to peace is in schedule management. Learning what consistent timeblocks you are working with for finishing schoolwork, taking personal time, and performing while in uniform is the ultimate method for maintaining the expectations you, and others, have set for yourself.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Whether you utlize the calendar and task management services on your smart phone, or invest in a management service app, it&rsquo;s important to find the method most usable to you.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:17pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Join Vixory Today&nbsp;</span></span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Vixory is here to connect student athletes with college recruiters and coaches that will lead them toward their future career. We care about our student athletes that register with us, and work to provide them an optimal experience. If you are interested in athletic transfer, we&rsquo;d love to hear from you! Follow our link to </span></span></span><a href=\"https://vixory.com/registration\" style=\"text-decoration:none\"><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><u>register today.&nbsp;</u></span></span></span></a></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2021-09-26 05:46:44','2022-01-17 23:34:11','How to Balance Expectations For Academics, Athletics, and Autonomy by Vixory','Vixory focuses on providing transferring college athletes with an informed approach of athletic transfer management in order to better assist student athletes as they enter into their future careers.',0,'U76tCWjcwskAV59CmxZKgHHPs7k4pTdZmjU45ZiP.jpg','Vixory focuses on providing transferring college athletes with an informed approach of athletic transfer management in order to better assist student athletes as they enter into their future careers.'),(9,'When Is The Best Time for A College Transfer? Vixory Answers',2,'<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Investing in the opportunity to be a student-athlete requires commitment and focus. This is because attending a university as an athlete is equivalent to having a full-time job. The field becomes your office, and your teammates are your coworkers.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Every now and then the environment in the office isn&rsquo;t the right fit, or the coach sees more potential for the student in another department. This is where the student- athlete college transfer process comes into play.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">The transfer process can be long and tedious if not attended to correctly. Vixory understands this and works hard to provide clarity support during this time. In today&rsquo;s blog, Vixory will highlight a few key elements to keep in mind when considering beginning the college transfer process.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:16pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Wait If You Aren&rsquo;t Sure</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">It&rsquo;s a big decision to decide to move on from a school you&rsquo;ve signed to. Careful consideration is recommended when you decide to tell your coach you plan on moving on, as well as taking the time to consider any financial consequences that could occur.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Beginning the college transfer process before you are ready can potentially become detrimental to current financial aid you might be receiving, or future aid that can be awarded.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Checking with financial aid, the registrar, and your advisor first, and notifying them you&rsquo;re considering a transfer is preferred.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">They will have access to resources you will need, and can confirm how your aid will be affected at the school you currently attend.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Having a school that is interested in signing you on, as well as carefully weighing all of your odds first, before making a decision will help you in the long run.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:16pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Follow The NCAA Transfer Rules</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Believe it or not, there are actual rules associated with the division of school you attend, your personal sport, and the level of aid you receive as a student-athlete.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">The NCAA has provided a special </span></span></span><a href=\"https://www.ncaa.org/student-athletes/current/transfer-terms\" style=\"text-decoration:none\"><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><u>rule book</u></span></span></span></a><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"> to follow when engaging in the college transfer process.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Becoming well-versed in these rules and regulations as you begin your journey will help you stay eligible to be an NCAA registered athlete, and will protect your team during the season. Having ineligible players on a team will definitely jeopardize your team&rsquo;s eligibility to compete.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Related Post: </span></span></span><a href=\"https://vixory.com/blog/What%20NCAA%20Transfer%20Rule%20Changes%20Mean%20for%20You\" style=\"text-decoration:none\"><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><u>What NCAA Transfer Rule Changes Mean For You</u></span></span></span></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:16pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">You Are No Longer Required To Sit Out During Transfer</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">In previous years it was important to be aware that certain Division I student-athletes and sports require one year of absence from playing after a transfer.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">This term was called &lsquo;redshirting&rsquo;. It exists to allow both for proper adjustment time for the new player, as well as assurance of fairness for game strategy between the universities the student is transferring between.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Per the new NCAA rules, &lsquo;redshirting&rsquo; is no longer required to play once an NCAA sanctioned transfer occurs. Sport specific rules should still be reviewed, and contacting an NCAA official to verify your transfer is set to go is still recommended.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:17pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Let Vixory Guide Your Steps&nbsp;</span></span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Vixory is here to help you launch into your future career. We create connection opportunities for athletes and universities around the nation. Our goal is to create an informed and thriving student-athlete community. If you have any questions on athletic transfer we&rsquo;d love to hear from you. Start the </span></span></span><a href=\"https://vixory.com/registration\" style=\"text-decoration:none\"><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><u>registration process</u></span></span></span></a><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"> and learn more about why Vixory is the perfect platform for you.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>','2021-10-21 01:40:03','2022-01-17 23:33:53','Vixory Explains The Best Time For College Transfers','In todays blog, Springfield, Mo based college transfer site Vixory covers the best time for student athletes to consider college transfers.',0,'WScWgeBZqkGULk2QOnwWoPwf0F9zLY1A7O2zqi4J.jpg','In todays blog, Springfield, Mo based college transfer site Vixory covers the best time for student athletes to consider college transfers.'),(10,'What To Expect After Your College Transfer, Vixory Offers Insight',2,'<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">So, you&rsquo;ve finished the lengthy process of reviewing your NCAA transfer rule subset specific to your sport, completed the appropriate paperwork between both institutions, and now you&rsquo;re at your new school.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:16pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Now What?</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Every athlete who has completed a college transfer has had this internal feeling as they step onto their new court or field. Luckily, Vixory understands this feeling and has some tips in today&rsquo;s blog on a few things to expect after completing your college transfer.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:16pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Expect An Adjustment Period </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">A university&rsquo;s athletic community is tightly knit.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Time spent traveling to games and tournaments paired with countless hours spent on team practice, personal workouts, and group workouts creates an unparalleled bonding experience.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">The team is your family, and until you graduate, your university&rsquo;s athletic program is your home. It&rsquo;s okay to have a period of &lsquo;displacement&rsquo; as you adjust to your new athletic family. Many players face low-level depression, loneliness, and stress when adjusting to a transfer.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Taking advantage of university-provided counseling services, speaking to your coach, and investing in connecting with your teammates will ease you through this period of emotional transition.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:16pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">New Team, New Family</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">This being said, you were given a place on this new team, by your new coach, for a reason. Don&rsquo;t let that slip away from you those first few months.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Coaches seek out players that are not only gifted in their physical abilities on the field, but they also seek out players that will naturally fit on their team.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Chances are, if you&rsquo;ve been recruited by your current coach, or were welcomed by a coach you reached out to, you belong on your new team. They know it, and you will learn it. Just give it time.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:16pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Focus Is Priority</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Bonding with your teammates is always important, but losing sight of your academic pathway is easily done during a time of transition.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">It can be so easy to forget about a short paper due next week, or to neglect to review your notes for that professor who favors pop quizzes.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">It&rsquo;s easy to want to substitute academic prep for more workout time, but it&rsquo;s important that you don&rsquo;t. Stay focused and utilize your new school&rsquo;s tutoring resources to help you adjust to the workload.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Related Post: </span></span></span><a href=\"https://vixory.com/blog/How%20To%20Keep%20Your%20Grades%20In%20Check%20Before%20College%20Transfer,%20Vixory%20Answers\" style=\"text-decoration:none\"><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><u>How To Keep Your Grades In Check Before College Transfer, Vixory Answers&nbsp;</u></span></span></span></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:17pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Join Vixory Today&nbsp;</span></span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Vixory is here to connect student-athletes with college recruiters and coaches that will lead them toward their future career. We care about our student-athletes that register with us, and work to provide them with an optimal experience. If you are interested in athletic transfer, we&rsquo;d love to hear from you! Follow our link to </span></span></span><a href=\"https://vixory.com/registration\" style=\"text-decoration:none\"><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><u>register today.&nbsp;</u></span></span></span></a></h2>','2021-11-05 19:36:46','2022-01-17 23:33:15','Vixory Explains What To Expect After Your College Transfer','In todays blog, Vixory explains what to expect after student athletes finish a college transfer.',0,'96obcjcQ1xxEnlAWBa4rzYVo5LvVS5o4P4wta9dS.jpg','In todays blog, Vixory explains what to expect after student athletes finish a college transfer.'),(11,'Vixory Offers Off-Season Conditioning Tips',2,'<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">On season routines are given, because of the mutual support coaches and teammates offer to student athletes to keep them fit and active.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:17pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Sleep, Eat Healthily, Drink Water</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">This one feels obvious, but properly caring for your body as a student-athlete is extremely important. Many young athletes forget to sleep full nights, and eat poorly because they feel they&rsquo;re invincible.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">If you are serious about becoming a career athlete, then prioritizing food that nourishes your body and resting should be your top priority.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:17pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Warm-Ups &amp; Cool-Downs</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">To avoid tearing ligaments or overstretching muscles it&rsquo;s important to remember to do your warm-ups and cool-downs.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Get into a flow of doing a 2-minute stretch with a mile to warm up your muscles, and some yoga stretches to finish the workout.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Your body will thank you for remembering to trigger some relaxation within your muscles.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:17pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Strength &amp; Cardio Balance</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Finding a balance between workouts that grow your muscles, and workouts that promote cardio and endurance is hard.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Some young athletes prefer to simply do the one they like best. However, to build proper endurance and flexibility it&rsquo;s important to find a balance between cardio and strength training.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Alternating workouts, or engaging in HIIT between weights is a great way to find that balance. You don&rsquo;t spend a ton of time on one or the other, and you achieve your desired results.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:17pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Make Time For Mental Health</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">It&rsquo;s so important to remember that your mental health is your biggest asset as a student-athlete. Your mindset is what will set you apart from other athletes.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Exercising your mental endurance is just as important as your physical endurance. So establishing mental boundaries, and mental support the same way you do for physical workouts is key.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Take advantage of your onsite counseling services, even in off-season--the door to the counseling office is open. Open up with your friends and ask for help if you feel down. Call your family.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">All of these small acts of personal service will help you build mental endurance as you balance school with athletics.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:17pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Register For Vixory Today!</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">At Vixory we care about student athletes and will work to provide as smooth a transfer process as possible. If you&rsquo;re a transferring student-athlete, or simply want to keep up with the community, sign up with us today! We&rsquo;re looking forward to connecting with you!</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2021-12-12 14:44:20','2022-01-17 23:32:57','Vixory Offers Off-Season Conditioning Tips','In todays blog, Vixory will offer advice on off-season conditioning to stay in shape for the upcoming season.',0,'jI1Th2MQA66lfYqe47fDA6kVNQ8AIm7vWUOBALvc.jpg','In todays blog, Vixory will offer advice on off-season conditioning to stay in shape for the upcoming season.'),(12,'Can Vixory Help With College Registration?',3,'<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">The college registration process is full of minute details that are easily missed. Vixory understands this and works hard to alleviate the transition from high school to college athletics for athletes seeking to register for college. In today&rsquo;s blog, our team at Vixory offers some key tips to remember when preparing for college registration as a student-athlete.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:17pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Don&rsquo;t Procrastinate</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">It&rsquo;s important to just get started. That&rsquo;s often the hardest part of the registration process: picking a school and going for it.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">The sooner you decide to begin pinpointing a school, or group of schools, you can begin reaching out about registering as a student-athlete.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:17pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Don&rsquo;t Forget Your Resume</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Even student athletes have to submit resumes when going to college. In fact, the student-athlete college application process is often more in depth than a traditional academic student process.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Student-athletes are expected to submit resumes and portfolios of their high school stats, letters of recommendation from coaches or teachers, and your high school experience.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">It is also important to start the process of reaching out to coaches </span></span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><em>before</em></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"> the registration period begins, so they have time to respond. Never pursue only one option. Always have a few open to you until you sign for one school specifically.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">If you make it known you are interviewing openly, it&#39;ll make the school most interested in you want to sign you faster. This ensures your place on the team, scholarship options, and allows you to begin your next step.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:17pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Contact The Registrar Office</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">It is important to get in touch with both your future school coach, but also the registrar office of your future college.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">The registrar&rsquo;s office will review all of your information to make sure your transcripts are received, your FAFSA is on file, your athlete paperwork is processed, and scholarships are lined up.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">You don&rsquo;t want to miss out on an incredible opportunity due to missing a small detail. The registrar&rsquo;s office can help.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:17pt\"><span style=\"font-