What can you do to simplify the process? Our team at Vixory can certainly help. In today&rsquo;s blog, Vixory discusses three simple steps that any collegiate student-athlete can take to ensure their transfer process moves smoothly.&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:17pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:#000000\">Gather the Right Information</span></span></span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:#000000\">The first step to take that helps ensure your transfer is simple: gather all of the important information required to make this decision! Deciding to transfer can be difficult, so before you do anything, make sure that you are well informed and understand what you can expect as you move forward through the process. If you&rsquo;re a student-athlete that desires a transfer, here are some things to consider first:&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:#000000\">What are your dream schools?</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:#000000\">Do your top schools offer the academic program you want?&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:#000000\">Where can you be successful athletically and academically?</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"list-style-type:decimal\"><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:#000000\">Do you have any financial limitations?</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:#000000\">Listing out your most pressing questions will help you know what to discuss with school officials, coaches, and your family. Once you have this completed, spend time researching the answers you need to make the best decision possible. Depending on the school you are transferring from, the process may look slightly different. If you are looking to transfer to or from a DI or DII school, be sure to educate yourself on the </span></span></span></span><a href=\"https://vixory.com/blog/Transfer%20Differences%20in%20DI%20versus%20DII,%20V\" style=\"text-decoration:none\"><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><u><span style=\"background-color:#000000\">DI transfer and DII transfer process</span></u></span></span></span></a><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:#000000\"> differences. If you are transferring from a DIII, JUCO, or NAIA school, first decide what division of college sports you would like to move into, and research their specific transfer processes.&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:17pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:#000000\">Enter the Transfer Portal&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:#000000\">Once you feel equipped with the right information, you can begin the process by entering into the </span></span></span></span><a href=\"http://s3.amazonaws.com/static.ncaa.org/static/champion/what-the-ncaa-transfer-portal-is/index.html\" style=\"text-decoration:none\"><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><u><span style=\"background-color:#000000\">NCAA transfer portal</span></u></span></span></span></a><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:#000000\">. To do this, you will need to inform your current coach and school administrator of your intent to transfer, which will prompt their compliance team to submit your name into the transfer portal within two business days. If you have a good relationship with your current school&rsquo;s coaching staff, these conversations can be hard to initiate. Transferring athletes will typically thank their coaches for the opportunity to represent the school and compete on its behalf and then describe the reasons why they feel a transfer is in their best interest. Once your current school is informed and your name is added to the transfer portal, you can have complete contact with other schools about the possibility of a transfer.&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"background-color:#000000\">Related Post:</span></strong></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:#000000\"> </span></span></span></span><a href=\"https://vixory.com/blog/What%20Are%20Myths%20Associated%20With%20College%20T\" style=\"text-decoration:none\"><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><u><span style=\"background-color:#000000\">What Are the Myths Associated With College Transfers?</span></u></span></span></span></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:17pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:#000000\">Communicate with Schools</span></span></span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:#000000\">With your name entered into the NCAA transfer portal, school officials and coaches are allowed to contact you with interest in recruiting you to their teams. During this phase of the process, you can help ensure a smooth transfer by maintaining great contact with all coaches who have reached out to you. Also, be sure to personally reach out to the schools you are most interested in, even if they haven&rsquo;t contacted you first! You must ask the right questions and be transparent with the schools you are interested in, that way, you can be confident that your next school meets your criteria and sets you up for a win in the classroom and on the field. As a prospective transfer, you have essentially been given a second chance in the recruiting process, so take full advantage of it!</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:17pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:#000000\">Vixory Makes the Transfer Process Easier</span></span></span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><span style=\"background-color:#000000\">If you are a collegiate student-athlete interested in transferring to a different school, you can help expedite the process by joining Vixory! With our state-of-the-art platform, you can post highlight videos, stats, and other information that is kept anonymous for other coaches to review. Once you&rsquo;ve entere