/span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">For many high school athletes, a full-ride athletic scholarship is a dream. As the name implies, this type of athletic scholarship covers the entire tuition cost for an incoming athlete.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Even better, some universities offer a more comprehensive version of a full-ride scholarship, which includes the entirety of necessary costs for a student-athlete&#39;s college experience (tuition, books, housing, and supplies). As full-ride scholarships are rare, the athlete must be among the best in their respective sport and be academically eligible based on the institution&#39;s standards.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Full-ride athletic scholarships can be given to any qualifying athlete that a coach is looking to sign, as long as the university provides the coach with enough budget for scholarships. Full-ride scholarship options are only available for sports that bring in revenue for most schools.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:17pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Partial Athletic Scholarship</span></span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">For athletes who do not play big-revenue sports or would like to attend a smaller university, partial athletic scholarships are great options! While some coaches can offer full-ride scholarships, others are given a specific budget in scholarship money divided among their recruiting class.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">As the scholarship amounts are separated, while they may not cover the entire cost of college education, they are still a great way to make the university experience affordable!</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><strong>Related Post:</strong></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"> </span></span></span><a href=\"https://vixory.com/blog/Vixory%20Explains%20the%20College%20Recruitment%20\" style=\"text-decoration:none\"><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><u>Vixory Explains the College Recruitment Process</u></span></span></span></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:17pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Walk-on Opportunities&nbsp;</span></span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">As recruiting classes fill up very quickly, a student-athlete&#39;s first choice in a university may have already allocated their entire scholarship budget for the year. Walk-on opportunities are a great way to join the team you want and potentially earn a future scholarship opportunity at your top school. Here are the two different types of walk-on opportunities:&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><strong>Recruited Walk-ons</strong></span></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">This type of walk-on opportunity means that a coach is interested in the athlete but without financial assistance offered. However, the athlete can always earn their financial aid through an athletic scholarship while competing for a spot on the team as a recruited walk-on.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><strong>Unrecruited Walk-ons</strong></span></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Unrecruited walk-ons qualify academically for admission into the university and attempt to join the team through an open try-out. In most cases, it&#39;s necessary to communicate with the college coach and ensure that a try-out opportunity is available.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:17pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Find New Athletic Scholarships with Vixory</span></span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">If you are a collegiate student-athlete and interested in new athletic scholarship opportunities at different schools, Vixory can help! We offer a free-to-use platform that anonymously connects student-athletes with college recruiters and coaches, allowing you to showcase your highlights, stats, and other information. To learn more about Vixory and how we help athletes land at their dream schools, </span></span></span><a href=\"https://vixory.com/\" style=\"text-decoration:none\"><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><u>contact us</u></span></span></span></a><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"> online today!</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2022-05-16 19:36:13','2022-05-16 19:36:13','What Are The Different Athletic Scholarships Available to Student-Athletes? Vixory 