report9/\" style=\"text-decoration:none\"><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><u>National Student Clearinghouse</u></span></span></span></a><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">, close to one-third of college students transfer to a different institution before receiving their degree. For collegiate student-athletes, the reasons that prompt a transfer can come from two different sides &mdash; an academic side, and an athletic side.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">In today&rsquo;s blog, the team at Vixory takes a look at the variety of reasons why student-athletes decide to switch universities, and why it might be time to consider a college transfer.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:17pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Desire to Compete in Higher Divisions</span></span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">A top reason why student-athletes are prompted to transfer colleges is because of the success they&rsquo;ve had at their current school. After months of practice, training, and competing in their respective conferences, many JUCO, NAIA, and DIII athletes find themselves among the top performers in the nation &ndash; thus initiating the desire to level up.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Competing at higher levels increases an athlete&rsquo;s chance to be scouted for professional teams and enjoy the perks that come with representing larger universities. If you find yourself among the elite in your division of play, is it time to consider potential options at a more competitive division?</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:17pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Not a Fitting Environment</span></span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Another reason why student-athletes desire a transfer is because of the environment or community they&rsquo;ve found at their current university. Whether it be due to the academic environment, the athletic environment, or even the geographical location of the university, many student-athletes find that they do not feel &ldquo;at home&rdquo; after their first year.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">If a college athlete has an issue with the dynamic of their team, coaching staff, or perhaps the experience not meeting their expectations, the decision to transfer weighs heavy on their mind. The institution&rsquo;s atmosphere is another important factor to consider. After all, you&rsquo;ll be spending the next 3-4 years of your life living there.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><strong>Related Post:</strong></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"> </span></span></span><a href=\"https://vixory.com/blog/How%20Collegiate%20Student-Athletes%20Can%20Ensu\" style=\"text-decoration:none\"><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\"><u>How to Ensure a College Transfer</u></span></span></span></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:17pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Financial Situation&nbsp;</span></span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">As tuition increases, unforeseen expenses arise, and financial statuses change; many athletes rethink attendance at their present college. A college transfer is often considered in situations where an athlete can receive more financial aid through athletic and/or academic scholarships at a separate university.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Sometimes, it&rsquo;s in the student-athletes best interest to move to a school where in-state tuition is offered, as long as they have a desire to compete in their sport with that school&rsquo;s team.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:17pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Academic Pursuits&nbsp;</span></span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Some athletes consider a transfer if their academic major is no longer offered, or if they decide to pursue an entirely different type of degree. If this is the reason that prompts a college transfer, it&rsquo;s generally best for this type of transfer to occur towards the beginning of a student-athlete&rsquo;s career versus the latter part of their career. Any student who moves to a different university could face challenges with transferring credits, especially for higher-level courses that are taken towards the end of college experiences.&nbsp;</span></span></span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><span style=\"color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size:17pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Montserrat,sans-serif\">Find New Athletic Scholarships with Vixory</span></span></span></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://vixory.com/\" style=\"text-decoration:none\